    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🎯 Workflow Overview\n\nThis workflow demonstrates enterprise-grade inquiry triage with:\n\n**1. Form Capture** - Collect client details\n**2. Client Lookup** - Retrieve ownership & history\n**3. RAG Retrieval** - Find similar past cases\n**4. AI Analysis** - Context-aware classification\n**5. Smart Routing** - Escalate or auto-process\n\n**Key Features:**\n• Email-based client identification\n• Historical case similarity matching\n• Sentiment-based urgency detection\n• Automated response generation\n• Human review for high-priority cases",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 320,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "5825a353-c655-4b31-9eec-d5ccc1b21380",
      "name": "Workflow Guide",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        160,
        208
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔧 Configuration Required\n\n**Backend API Endpoints:**\n1. Client Lookup: `GET /api/client/context?email=...`\n2. RAG Search: `POST /api/rag/search`\n\n**Mock Response Examples:**\n```json\n// Client Context\n{\n  \"client_exists\": true,\n  \"client_id\": 381,\n  \"client_type\": \"Existing\",\n  \"assigned_consultant\": \"Sarah Johnson\",\n  \"past_inquiries_count\": 12,\n  \"active_projects\": [\"Manager Transition\"]\n}\n\n// RAG Similar Cases\n{\n  \"similar_cases\": [\n    {\n      \"inquiry_id\": 1001,\n      \"category\": \"Strata Management Change\",\n      \"actions_taken\": [...],\n      \"resolution\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**For MVP Testing:**\nReplace HTTP Request nodes with mock data using Set nodes.",
        "height": 612,
        "width": 540,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "5a8cec2c-4cbe-4118-b2de-79546fdd7f1a",
      "name": "Setup Instructions",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        160,
        736
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI Model Settings\n\n**Current Configuration:**\n• Model: gpt-4o-mini\n• Temperature: 0.2 (low for consistent classification)\n• Max Tokens: 1000\n\n**Why Low Temperature?**\nFor triage/classification tasks, we want deterministic, consistent results. Temperature 0.2 ensures the AI follows classification rules strictly.\n\n**Adjust in:** OpenAI Model node → Options → Temperature",
        "height": 240,
        "width": 320,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "1c87e41f-3c8a-49ac-8347-674451b03c31",
      "name": "AI Configuration",
